1. Start the Environment
Run the following command in your terminal. It should build the images and start the containers without errors.
code
Bash
docker-compose up -d --build
Check: Run docker ps. You should see three containers running: postgres, mock-server, and pipeline-service.
2. Verify Part 1: Flask Mock Server (Port 5000)
The mock server should serve the JSON data with pagination.
Health Check:
code
Bash
curl http://localhost:5000/api/health
# Expected: {"status": "healthy"}
Pagination Test:
code
Bash
curl "http://localhost:5000/api/customers?page=1&limit=5"
# Expected: 5 records, total: 21, page: 1, limit: 5
Single Customer:
code
Bash
curl http://localhost:5000/api/customers/CUST001
# Expected: JSON for John Doe
404 Handling:
code
Bash
curl -i http://localhost:5000/api/customers/NONEXISTENT
# Expected: HTTP 404 status
3. Verify Part 2: FastAPI Pipeline (Port 8000)
This service interacts with the database and the mock server.
Trigger Ingestion:
code
Bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/ingest
# Expected: {"status": "success", "records_processed": 21}
Verify Database Storage:
code
Bash
curl "http://localhost:8000/api/customers?page=1&limit=5"
# Expected: Data returned from PostgreSQL, not the JSON file.
Test Upsert Logic:
Run the ingest command again:
code
Bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/ingest
Then check the total count:
code
Bash
curl "http://localhost:8000/api/customers"
# Expected: "total" should still be 21.
# If it's 42, your upsert (merge) logic is failing.
4. Technical "Perfect" Checklist
Check your code against these specific requirements:

Auto-Pagination: Does pipeline-service/services/ingestion.py loop through pages if the mock server has more data than the limit? (My implementation does this using a while True loop).

dlt Merge: Does the dlt pipeline use write_disposition="merge"? (Required for the "Upsert" requirement).

Environment Variables: Are DATABASE_URL and MOCK_SERVER_URL used instead of hardcoded strings?

Health Checks: Does docker-compose.yml have a health check for Postgres to prevent the pipeline from crashing on startup?

Project Structure: Does your folder structure match the requested tree exactly?
Troubleshooting the "Dockerfile not found" error
If you still see the error failed to read dockerfile, ensure:
You are in the root directory (/workspaces/backend-assessment).
The Dockerfile in mock-server/ is named exactly Dockerfile (case-sensitive, no extension).
Your docker-compose.yml points to the folder: build: ./mock-server.
If all these tests pass, your submission is 100% complete and correct.